cc-flytrap – Local Proxy Utility

This project "cc-flytrap" is a local proxy utility that intercepts traffic between Claude Code and Anthropic's API for debugging and inspection purposes.

1. Local Interception Only

All network interception occurs locally on the user's machine. This tool does not forward, relay, or proxy traffic to any third party other than the intended API endpoint (api.anthropic.com).

2. No Data Exfiltration

This project does not collect, store, or transmit any user data to external servers. All intercepted data remains local and is discarded after processing.

3. No Affiliation or Endorsement

This project is not affiliated with, endorsed by, or sponsored by Anthropic PBC or its products (Claude, Claude Code, Claude.ai, etc.). It is an independent open-source utility.

4. No Circumvention of Protections

This tool does not bypass authentication, authorization, or security controls. Users must have valid API access. It merely modifies request payloads before forwarding—same API endpoint, same authentication, same billing.

5. User Responsibility

Users are solely responsible for ensuring their use of any third-party services complies with applicable terms of service. Modifying API payloads may result in errors (e.g., rate limits, server errors)—this is an expected API behavior.

